entry.title: Traverse nested ::marker inside ::before/::after
entry.content:
When list-style-image fails loading, we mark the element with the

list-style-image for NotifyOfSubtreeChange with ancestors marked

nested pseudo elements when you have a ::marker with a list-style-image

inside a ::before or ::after pseudo element.

traverse into the nested pseudo element and clears the ancestor bit on

the outer pseudo element.

entry.title: WebNN: Decouple command list recording from execution for DirectML
entry.content:
This CL mainly decouples the command list recording from execution

to optimize the graph execution performance for DirectML backend.



After refactoring the `dml::CommandRecorder` and `dml::GraphImpl`,

some detailed changes are:



1. `dml::CommandRecorder::Close()` and

`dml::CommandRecorder::Execute()` methods are added to decouple the

command list closing from execution.



2. `dml::GraphImpl::RecordGraphExecution()` method mainly records

the graph execution onto the command list, binds all required

resources and closes the command list.



The method is called firstly after the graph initialization has been

completed to prepare for the first graph execution. For following

graph executions, the method only needs to be called if we need to

record commands and bind resources again.



3. `dml::GraphImpl::ComputeImpl()` calls

`dml::CommandRecorder::Execute()` that submits the command list for

execution and references all required resources.



4. `dml::GraphImpl::PersistentResource` struct is introduced to

encapsulate the persistent buffer, its binding and description.

`dml::GraphImpl::OnCompilationComplete()` allocates it and pass it

along the way to the `dml::GraphImpl`.



Based on these changes, the most important benefit is that it avoids

re-calling the `IDMLCommandRecorder::RecordDispatch` and

`ID3D12GraphicsCommandList::Close` methods which may be time-consuming

for some devices during the first execution and following executions

of a graph if not needed.



Bug: 1273291

entry.title: Change the route of passing is_ad_resource flag
entry.content:
The renderer process's PageTimingMetricsSender accumulates resource data

usage information as PageResourceDataUse structure and sends it in

batches to the browser process.



The PageResourceDataUse structure contains the data usage information

(total_received_bytes_, encoded_body_length_, decoded_body_length_) and

the `reported_as_ad_resource_` flag. These data is used to measure the

data usage for ads.



Currently the data usage information and the ads flag are passed through

different route. This CL unifies them.



[1] For subresources:

The data usage information is passed from ResourceRequestSender:

ResourceRequestSender

->ResourceLoadInfoNotifierWrapper

->WeakWrapperResourceLoadInfoNotifier

->RenderFrameImpl

->MetricsRenderFrameObserver

->PageTimingMetricsSender

->PageResourceDataUse



The ads flags is passed from ResourceLoader:

ResourceLoader::DidReceiveResponse()

->ResourceLoadObserverForFrame::DidReceiveResponse()

->SubresourceFilter::ReportAdRequestId()

->WebDocumentSubresourceFilterImpl::ReportAdRequestId()

->AdResourceTracker::NotifyAdResourceObserved()

->MetricsRenderFrameObserver::OnAdResourceObserved()



This route of the flag was introduced by https://crrev.com/c/1165823 at

2018 when ResourceRequestSender couldn't know the flag.

But https://crrev.com/c/4983468 introduced `is_ad_tagged` flag in

network::ResourceRequest. So now ResourceRequestSender can sends

it to the PageResourceDataUse through the route for the data usage.



[2] For navigation resources:

The data usage information is passed from NavigationBodyLoader:

NavigationBodyLoader

->ResourceLoadInfoNotifierWrapper

->WeakWrapperResourceLoadInfoNotifier

->RenderFrameImpl

->MetricsRenderFrameObserver

->PageTimingMetricsSender

->PageResourceDataUse



The ads flags is passed from DocumentLoader:

DocumentLoader::SetSubresourceFilter()

->SubresourceFilter::SubresourceFilter()

->SubresourceFilter::ReportAdRequestId()

->WebDocumentSubresourceFilterImpl::ReportAdRequestId()

->AdResourceTracker::NotifyAdResourceObserved()

->MetricsRenderFrameObserver::OnAdResourceObserved()



This CL changes the route for the ads flag to pass the flag from

RenderFrameImpl through ResourceLoadInfoNotifierWrapper:



RenderFrameImpl::CommitNavigation()

->WebNavigationBodyLoader::FillNavigationParamsResponseAndBodyLoader()

->ResourceLoadInfoNotifierWrapper::NotifyResourceLoadInitiated()

->WeakWrapperResourceLoadInfoNotifier

->RenderFrameImpl

->MetricsRenderFrameObserver

->PageTimingMetricsSender

->PageResourceDataUse

entry.title: Pass PendingRemote<CodeCacheHost> for background on CommitNavigation
entry.content:
Currently one pending_remote is passed on

the CommitNavigation IPC (https://crrev.com/3033191). It is used only

for normal resource fetch from the main thread. When loading a resource

from the background thread, LoaderFactoryForFrame::

GetBackgroundCodeCacheHost() gets a new pending_remote of

blink.mojom.CodeCacheHost from BrowserInterfaceBroker. This is not good

for performance, because it can be blocked if the browser main thread

is busy.



This CL solves this problem by sending two pending_remotes of

CodeCacheHost on the CommitNavigation IPC, for the normal

resource fetch from the main thread and for the resource fetch from the

background thread.

entry.title: Refactor blink::ResourceLoader
entry.content:
This CL refactors blink::ResourceLoader as followings:

1. Introduce `network_resource_request_`. The constructor initializes

it, and set net::LOAD_ONLY_FROM_CACHE flag for cache aware loading.

2. Remove `ResourceRequestHead` argument from StartWith(), Restart(),

RequestSynchronously(), RequestAsynchronously(). And renames

StartWith() to StartFetch(). The `ResourceRequestHead` argument was

needed only for cache aware loading to modify

mojom::FetchCacheMode::kUnspecifiedOnlyIfCachedStrict flag from

`resource_->GetResourceRequest()`. But we don't need it because

we set net::LOAD_ONLY_FROM_CACHE flag in the constructor.

3. Stop creating `loader_` for data-URL requests. And introduce

`finished_` flag for `IsLoading()` checking.

4. Stop checking DownloadToBlob() flag for the

`CanHandleDataURLRequestLocally()` check. This flag is set only in

XMLHttpRequest::CreateRequest() which doesn't set it for data-URL

requests. (https://crrev.com/c/955957)

entry.title: [Site search policy] Do not delete existing SEs on conflict
entry.content:
TemplateURLService can handle multiple SEs with the same keyword

(mostly due to extensions), so there is no need to delete existing

SEs in case of keyword conflict.



This CL ensures that the policy is not destructive - existing search

engines are never deleted, even if the user has never interacted with

them. In case of a keyword conflict between site search and and existing

engine, the following ordering is applied:

- If a keyword starts with "@", prefer the one set by site search policy

- Otherwise, prefer the one set by site search policy only if the user

interacted with it



There is no reason to add any extra validation for conflicts with DSP

set by policy - the corresponding policy handlers already take care of

potential scenarios.



Interactions with DSP not set by policy will be handled separately

(b/314162426).

to the ClientView. This method allows various ClientViews to specify
